      108.02,
      482.33,
      155.78,
      496.33
    ],
    "text": "follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      503.33,
      543.31,
      533.71
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThe charge shall contain such particulars as to the time and place of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      540.8,
      543.34,
      554.86
    ],
    "text": "alleged offence and as to the person (if any) against whom and as to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      562.04,
      543.41,
      576.1
    ],
    "text": "thing (if any) in respect of which it was committed as are reasonably",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      583.16,
      543.33,
      597.22
    ],
    "text": "sufficient to give the accused notice of the matter with which he is charged",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      604.28,
      383.35,
      618.34
    ],
    "text": "and to show that the offence is not prescribed.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      646.52,
      543.89,
      660.52
    ],
    "text": "12. It is argued that a criminal charge must always state the precise time of",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      667.64,
      543.86,
      681.64
    ],
    "text": "the alleged offence. However, while the precise time should be included",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      688.78,
      543.72,
      702.78
    ],
    "text": "whenever possible, it is not absolutely necessary in every case. The true",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.28,
      333.17,
      755.76
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      72.0,
      543.7,
      86.0
    ],
    "text": "purpose of a charge is to provide the accused with adequate notice of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      93.12,
      525.72,
      107.18
    ],
    "text": "allegation so that a defence can be prepared and the trial remains fair.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      135.36,
      543.7,
      149.36
    ],
    "text": "13. In many offences, the exact time may not be known and requiring it",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      156.48,
      543.74,
      170.48
    ],
    "text": "would encourage artificial precision and lead to technical dismissals. In",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      177.6,
      543.73,
      191.6
    ],
    "text": "many cases, such as repeated abuse over several months, a victim may",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      198.72,
      543.67,
      212.72
    ],
    "text": "be able to describe the events and context but not the exact time. If the",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      219.99,
      543.72,
      233.99
    ],
    "text": "law demanded a specific time, regardless of the circumstances, it would",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      241.11,
      543.74,
      255.11
    ],
    "text": "either force the prosecution to speculate or prevent legitimate cases from",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      262.23,
      543.85,
      276.23
    ],
    "text": "being tried at all. Therefore, what matters is not precision for its own",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      283.35,
      543.89,
      297.35
    ],
    "text": "sake, but whether the charge provides sufficient notice to ensure a fair",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      304.47,
      139.46,
      318.53
    ],
    "text": "trial.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      346.71,
      543.68,
      360.71
    ],
    "text": "14. It may be argued that the time must always be stated because an",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      367.83,
      543.92,
      381.83
    ],
    "text": "accused may rely on an alibi. This concern is valid where the defence",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      388.97,
      543.93,
      402.97
    ],
    "text": "genuinely depends on a specific time. However, it does not justify an",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      410.09,
      543.76,
      424.09
    ],
    "text": "absolute rule. Stating the specific time of the offence in a charge is",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      431.21,
      446.26,
      445.21
    ],
    "text": "desirable but it is not absolutely necessary in every case.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      452.21,
      543.94,
      482.53
    ],
    "text": "15. The controlling principle should be whether the charge gives adequate",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      489.65,
      543.74,
      503.65
    ],
    "text": "notice and prevents prejudice to the accused because specific time is",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      510.77,
      451.3,
      524.77
    ],
    "text": "often unknown and not always an element of the offence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      553.16,
      543.94,
      567.16
    ],
    "text": "16. Section 166 of the Code of Criminal Procedure Act No. 15 of 1979 reads",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      574.28,
      172.82,
      588.28
    ],
    "text": "as follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      595.28,
      543.48,
      625.66
    ],
    "text": "\u201cAny error in stating either the offence or the particulars required to be",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      632.72,
      543.36,
      646.78
    ],
    "text": "stated in the charge and any omission to state the offence or those",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      653.84,
      543.32,
      667.9
    ],
    "text": "particulars shall not be regarded at any stage of the case as material,",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      674.96,
      448.9,
      689.02
    ],
    "text": "unless the accused was misled by such error or omission.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.28,
      333.17,
      755.76
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      72.0,
      543.76,
      86.0
    ],
    "text": "17. The appellant has presented a narrative denying the specific allegations",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      93.12,
      543.72,
      107.12
    ],
    "text": "contained within the charge. This action on its own fails to demonstrate",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      114.24,
      543.73,
      128.24
    ],
    "text": "the appellant was misled by any alleged omission in the charge.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      135.36,
      543.95,
      149.36
    ],
    "text": "Moreover, should such an omission be identified, it could be deemed",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      156.48,
      333.91,
      170.48
    ],
    "text": "immaterial and therefore disregarded.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      198.72,
      473.38,
      212.78
    ],
    "text": "18. In R Vs. Dossi 12 Cr. App. R. 158, it has been held as follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      219.87,
      543.28,
      250.25
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThat a date specified in an indictment is not a material matter unless it is",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      257.31,
      543.68,
      271.37
    ],
    "text": "an essential part of the alleged offence; the defendant maybe convicted",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      278.43,
      543.39,
      292.49
    ],
    "text": "although the Jury find that the offence was committed on a date other than",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      299.55,
      543.26,
      313.61
    ],
    "text": "that specified in the indictment. Amendment of the indictment is",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      320.67,
      543.36,
      334.73
    ],
    "text": "unnecessary, although it will be a good practice to do so (provided there is",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      341.79,
      543.72,
      355.85
    ],
    "text": "no prejudice) where it is clear on the evidence that if the offence was",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      362.91,
      526.92,
      376.97
    ],
    "text": "committed at all, it was committed on the day other than that specified.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      405.17,
      443.86,
      419.17
    ],
    "text": "19. In her testimony, PW01 refers to her birthday as follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      447.41,
      260.33,
      461.64
    ],
    "text": "\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb- \u0dad\u0db8\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9 \u0d8b\u0db4\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dc0\u0daf\u0daf?",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      468.77,
      194.57,
      483.0
    ],
    "text": "\u0d8b- 1999.04.27",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      490.01,
      479.62,
      504.24
    ],
    "text": "\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb- \u0d8b\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dad \u0daf\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9c\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc4\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf \u0dd9\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0daf?",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      510.77,
      144.74,
      525.0
    ],
    "text": "\u0d8b: \u0d94\u0dc0\u0dca.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      324.07,
      531.8,
      539.88,
      545.8
    ],
    "text": "[vide page 40 of the Appeal Brief]",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      564.8,
      543.93,
      578.8
    ],
    "text": "20. Crucially, the appellant has failed to dispute the date of birth provided by",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      586.04,
      543.81,
      600.04
    ],
    "text": "PW01 in her testimony. This critical piece of evidence has remained",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      607.16,
      543.84,
      621.16
    ],
    "text": "unchallenged throughout the proceedings. Indeed during the rigorous",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      628.28,
      543.74,
      642.28
    ],
    "text": "cross examination of pw01, the appellant\u2019s counsel has not presented or",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      649.4,
      543.73,
      663.4
    ],
    "text": "suggested any alternative date of birth or have they sought to impeach",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      670.52,
      341.83,
      684.52
    ],
    "text": "this specific aspect of PW01\u2019s evidence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.28,
      333.17,
      755.76
    ],
    "text": "Page 7 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      85.58,
      72.0,
      543.96,
      86.0
    ],
    "text": "21. It is a well-established principle of law that a fact presented in evidence,",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial",
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      93.12,
      543.86,
      107.12
    ],
    "text": "which is not actively challenged, contradicted or disputed by the",
    "fonts": [
      "Bookman Old Style"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      114.24,
      543.85,
      128.24
